  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Safe Schools in San Ram&#xF3;n</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to reduce conditions of vulnerability for schoolchildren and teachers in the Rural Educational Areas (NER) of La Corona and La Garita in the municipality of San Ram&#xF3;n, Department of Matagalpa, by promoting the Safe School model that build s knowledge, awareness, and practices around Risk Management and Climate Change Adaptation. Specifically, it will develop the Disaster Risk Reduction capacity of adults and children in 23 schools in the 2 areas; as well as improve access to potable water and improved sanitation in 4 schools. In total the project will directly benefit 2,004 women and girls and 1,269 men and boys</narrative>
  </description>
